Description           
	Phosphorus is a highly reactive element. It is never found as a free element on Earth. It has a concentration in the Earth's crust of about one gram per kilogram. It is colorless, waxy white, yellow, scarlet, red, violet and black  in appearance. Phosphorus has several allotropes that exhibits strikingly different properties. the two most common allotropes are white phosphorous and red phosphorous. White phosphorous is the most important form of elemental phosphorous.